Our Programs
Our programs are designed to improve STEM education inside and out. We’ve built all of our learning resources with the NGSS and local state standards as a foundation.




STEM Curriculum
Learn about STEM curriculum that ignites imagination.



Science Labs
Ardusat’s engaging and interactive science labs are designed for schools, with a full set of classroom management tools and resources.



Space Labs
Bring real data from space into the classroom.



Professional Development
Explore workshops, demos and webinars meant to help you develop your professional skills and expand your knowledge.











Students in Santa Rosa County are learning to problem solve, use mathematics, and utilize science concepts when we're using the Ardusat program. It's getting them ready for the future and where we need them to be.


Susan Still, 5th Grade Teacher







STEM Curriculum that Ignites Imagination







Our instructional design team is constantly creating exciting experiments and curriculum which use Arduinos, sensors, data, coding, and more. Apply these classroom-ready resources right away, or personalize them to fit your learning objectives. It’s simple to add modules and edit lesson plans.







Once you’ve assigned an experiment to your class, your students can take notes, ask questions, and collect data right in the experiment. Share your projects with other teachers, or search the eHub and be inspired by other experiments.










Science Labs for Classrooms
Purpose-Built for Schools
Ardusat’s engaging and interactive science labs are designed for schools, with a full set of classroom management tools and resources.

Set up multiple classes.
Import rosters.
Assign experiments to individuals or teams.
Review completed experiments.







Flexible, Classroom-Ready Resources
All labs are easy to integrate into current curriculum, so you can use them right away or personalize them to fit your learning objectives.







Intuitive STEM Curriculum
With Ardusat’s intuitive content and professional development, teachers don’t need to have an engineering background to teach engineering concepts, or a technology background to teach technical content.







Powerful Tools
Students conduct exciting experiments right in the platform, capturing data in eHub and utilizing its powerful graphing and logging tools to analyze findings.












Launch Your School's Space Program





Make Space Accessible
Ardusat gives schools the tools to grant students access to space like never before and without the high costs.









How It Works
Our Mission Control team will help your students design their experiments, which includes: choosing sensors, collection frequencies, and locations around the globe, that will deliver the kind of data real scientists work with. Through our partnership with Spire we’ll run your experiment in space and deliver back the data the satellites collect.








Real-Time Satellite Tracking
With our live satellite tracker, your class will be able to monitor their experiment every step of the way. See what other schools are doing in space right now.


View Satellites











Training Options to Suit Your Needs
We have numerous professional development options to help you get started and expand your knowledge. Request onsite and online sessions, or watch recorded training at your convenience.








Workshops




Engineering For Science Teachers
Four hour, onsite training for science teachers who want to incorporate engineering into their curriculum. Learn More.



Learning Outcomes:

Identify engineering role in science courses
Use Arduino and sensors to collect and analyze data
Troubleshoot technology related problems
Identify engineering projects appropriate for course


Topics:
            Arduino, Troubleshooting, Sensors, Experiments, Code, Engineering, Engineering Process.
          

Benefits:
            Increases hands on projects in the classroom, increases faculty comfort level with engineering, increases student problems solving skills.
          





NGSS Your Science Curriculum
Eight hour, onsite training for science teachers that covers the Engineering for Science Teachers Ardusat workshop with NGSS aspects Learn More.



Learning Outcomes:

Identify engineering role in science courses
Use Arduino and sensors to collect and analyze data
Troubleshoot technology related problems
Identify engineering projects appropriate for course
Run inquiry based lesson
Increase problem solving
Describe three parts of standards (core ideas, crosscutting concepts, practices)
Build assessment tools for NGSS activities


Topics:
            Arduino, troubleshooting, sensors, experiments, code, engineering, engineering process, NGSS practices, NGSS disciplinary core ideas, NGSS crosscutting concepts, building models, asking questions, data analysis.
          

Benefits:
            Makes NGSS implementations easy, supplies teachers with lessons and assessment plans that are in line with NGSS.
          





Ardusat Launch Pack Getting Started for Teachers
Two hour, online training for science teachers who have purchased a launch pack or sensor kit. Learn More.



Learning Outcomes:

Identify parts in kit
Connect components to Arduino
Upload code to Arduino
Identify sensors on space board
Collect data for experiment
Run eHub experiment
Customize eHub experiments


Topics:
            Arduino, space board, sensor kit, experiments, eHub, troubleshooting, DemoSat, expansion collection.
          

Benefits:
            Provides teachers with a fast, guided method to learn about the basics.
          





Learn by Experimenting with Ardusat
Two hour, onsite training for science teachers who want to learn more about incorporating labs in their classroom. Learn More.



Learning Outcomes:

Connect components to Arduino
Upload code to Arduino
Identify sensors on space board
Collect data for experiment
Run eHub experiment


Topics:
            Arduino, space board, sensor kit, experiments, eHub, troubleshooting, DemoSat, expansion collection.
          

Benefits:
            Builds excitement and enthusiasm for hands on projects; introduces teachers to the world of Arduino, code, and sensors; creates an “I did that!” moments for students.
          





Learn by Watching
Three hour, onsite training (plus a short planning call) to observe an instructor teaching Arduinos, NGSS, coding, etc. Learn More.



Learning Outcomes:
Customizable based on need

Topics:
            Arduino, troubleshooting, sensors, experiments, code, engineering, engineering process, NGSS, eHub, DemoSat, etc.
          

Benefits:
            Provides teachers with pre-session and post-session coaching and a live teaching example.
          









