Company Overview of Ardusat, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Ardusat, Inc., an educational technology company, operates an educational platform, which provides tools for educators that help science and math students to learn from satellites in space. The company offers a space kit, which provides access to learning resources that teach about the sensors that are used by classrooms to create and run space experiments. It offers an open satellite platform that enables the general public to design and run applications, games, and experiments in space while steering onboard cameras to take pictures on-demand; and students to conduct experiments by controlling integrated sensors, such as spectrometers, magnetometers, radiation measurement devices, gyroscop...
Ardusat, Inc., an educational technology company, operates an educational platform, which provides tools for educators that help science and math students to learn from satellites in space. The company offers a space kit, which provides access to learning resources that teach about the sensors that are used by classrooms to create and run space experiments. It offers an open satellite platform that enables the general public to design and run applications, games, and experiments in space while steering onboard cameras to take pictures on-demand; and students to conduct experiments by controlling integrated sensors, such as spectrometers, magnetometers, radiation measurement devices, gyroscopes, accelerometers, and thermometers. The company also operates an online store for DemoSats, space kits, classroom launch packs, T-shirts, logo stickers, space kit expansion products, logging expansion kits, rechargeable batteries, and wireless expansion kits. Ardusat, Inc. was founded in 2012 and is based in Sandy, Utah.
Detailed Description


